title: Caribbean Airlines Flights Disrupted Due To Closure of Jamaican Air SpaceTravelandtourworld.com
text:
Caribbean Airlines Flights Disrupted Due To Closure of Jamaican Air Space Published on : Tuesday, August 25, 2015
Caribbean Airlines advises that due to ongoing industrial action by air traffic controllers in Jamaica, the country’s air space has been shut down resulting in disruptions to the following Caribbean Airlines flights:
BW 078, Saturday August 22nd – departing Lester B. Pearson International, Toronto, Canada to Norman Manley International, Kingston, Jamaica
BW 0031, Saturday August 22nd – departing Norman Manley International, Kingston, Jamaica to Fort Lauderdale, Hollywood International, Florida
BW 0030, Saturday August 22nd – departing Fort Lauderdale, Hollywood International, Florida to Montego Bay, Jamaica
BW 016, Saturday August 22nd – departing John F. Kennedy International, New York to Norman Manley International, Kingston, Jamaica
Caribbean Airlines has activated its call out plan to contact customers travelling on these services.
